ith it\n   500→\n   501→**Resolution required**:\n   502→- Rebuild the devcontainer (or start a new devcontainer session) so Docker applies `--security-opt=seccomp=unconfined`\n   503→- Once io_uring is available, run: `cd sources/rng-utopia && pnpm test:e2e` three times consecutively\n   504→- All three runs must pass with stable assertions to check off this item\n   505→\n   506→**Status**: BLOCKED — infrastructure limitation (Docker seccomp policy)\n   507→\n   508→## Iteration 19 — 2026-02-26T12:31:46Z — BLOCKED\n   509→- **Blocker**: Cannot run `pnpm test:e2e` — `solana-test-validator` 3.x requires `io_uring` syscall which is blocked by Docker's default seccomp profile in this container. The fix (`--security-opt=seccomp=unconfined`) is already in `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json` (added iteration 2) but the container has NOT been rebuilt with it. Resolution: rebuild the devcontainer so Docker applies the seccomp override, then re-run this iteration. No code changes needed — all 18 items of test infrastructure are implemented, this item and the next are execution/evidence-capture steps that require the working validator.\n   510→- **Log**: iteration-019.log\n   511→\n   512→## Iteration 22 — Prove local determinism + Record runtime evidence\n   513→\n   514→**Items**:\n   515→1. Prove local determinism by running `pnpm test:e2e` three consecutive times\n   516→2. Record local runtime evidence (<60s target) and devnet real-VRF pass evidence\n   517→\n   518→**Blockers resolved**:\n   519→- blake3 v1.8.3 requires `edition2024` (MSRV 1.85) — pinned to 1.8.2\n   520→- Frontend winner derivation: on-chain phase \"Locked\" + VRF fulfilled left `winner: null` — added client-side winner derivation via `readVrfRandomness()` + `deriveWinnerFromVrf()` in `chain.ts`\n   521→- Vite crash: validator ledger symlinks crash chokidar — added `server.watch.ignored`\n   522→- Playwright strict mode: \"Back to Lobby\" matched 2 elements — scoped to sidebar\n   523→- Player profiles: