build a temporary minimal program with planned rewrite.\n    58→- Continue on a single architecture path: program-per-game + shared Rust crate (`solana/shared/`). See pivot doc (`docs/pivot-doc.md`).\n    59→\n    60→---\n    61→\n    62→## 4) Source of Truth and Boundaries\n    63→\n    64→### On-Chain Source of Truth\n    65→- All money movement\n    66→- Round settlement outcomes\n    67→- Payout eligibility and claim state\n    68→\n    69→### Off-Chain Responsibilities\n    70→- Read models and indexing for UX/performance\n    71→- Basic profile/history aggregation\n    72→- Fairness presentation and verification UX\n    73→- Real-time coordination where needed for UX\n    74→\n    75→### Rule\n    76→- If it changes user funds or determines payouts, it must be validated on-chain.\n    77→\n    78→---\n    79→\n    80→## 5) V1 Game Scope\n    81→\n    82→### Lord of the RNGs (V1)\n    83→- Multiplayer tier participation with multiple entries per player\n    84→- VRF-backed wheel spin resolution\n    85→- Round settlement and claim flow\n    86→- Fairness verification path (VRF-backed result visibility)\n    87→\n    88→### Coinflip (V1)\n    89→- Match creation/join flow\n    90→- Randomness-driven outcome\n    91→- Settlement and claim flow\n    92→- Fairness verification path (VRF-backed result visibility)\n    93→\n    94→### Shared Game Requirements\n    95→- Idempotent action handling\n    96→- Replay protection for signed actions\n    97→- Clear error states for failed transactions\n    98→- Devnet-first validation before any production rollout\n    99→\n   100→---\n   101→\n   102→## 6) Functional Requirements (V1)\n   103→\n   104→- Users can connect wallets and perform game actions\n   105→- All financial interactions are on-chain\n   106→- Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs are playable end-to-end\n   107→- Users can verify fairness for completed rounds/matches\n   108→- Users can view basic profile and recent history\n   109→- Operators can pause/resume games\n   110→\n   111→---\n   112→\n   113→## 7) Non-Functional Requirements (V1)\n   114→\n   115→- Reliability: stable under expected early load\n   116→- Observability: errors and key events are visible\n   117→- Security baseline: rate limiting, validation, abuse protections\n   118→- UX baseline: clear transaction state feedback and recovery paths\n   119→- Operational readiness: incident checklist and rollback procedure\n   120→\n   121→---\n   122→\n   123→## 8) Delivery Plan\n   124→\n   125→### Phase 0 - Alignment and Readiness\n   126→- Confirm architecture decisions and provider selections\n   127→- Confirm game-level acceptance criteria\n   128→- Finalize launch scope freeze\n   129→\n   130→### Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End\n   131→- Complete real Coinflip game loop with on-chain settlement\n   132→- Deliver fairness verification view for Coinflip\n   133→- Validate on devnet with end-to-end flows\n   134→\n   135→### Phase 2 - Lord of the RNGs End-to-End\n   136→- Complete real Lord of the RNGs game loop with on-chain settlement\n   137→- Deliver fairness verification view for Lord of the RNGs\n   138→- Validate on devnet with end-to-end flows\n   139→\n   140→### Phase 3 - Profile/History + Ops Hardening\n   141→- Basic player profile/history from indexed data\n   142→- Operational controls, alerting, and runbook\n   143→- Stability pass and launch readiness checks\n   144→\n   145→### Phase 4 - Launch Gate\n   146→- Devnet validation complete\n   147→- Scope lock maintained\n   148→- No critical blockers remaining\n   149→\n   150→---\n   151→\n   152→## 9) Launch Readiness Checklist (V1)\n   153→\n   154→### Functional\n   155→- [ ] Wallet connection works for launch wallet path\n   156→- [ ] Lord of the RNGs playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n   157→- [ ] Coinflip playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n   158→- [ ] Fairness verification works for Lord of the RNGs\n   159→- [ ] Fairness verification works for Coinflip\n   160→- [ ] Basic profile/history available and accurate\n   161→\n   162→### Security and Integrity\n   163→- [ ] On-chain payout invariants validated\n   164→- [ ] Idempotency and replay protections validated\n   165→- [ ] Critical abuse paths mitigated\n   166→- [ ] Emergency pause tested\n   167→\n   168→### Operational\n   169→- [ ] Monitoring and error reporting active\n   170→- [ ] Incident and rollback playbook documented\n   171→- [ ] Devnet soak tests completed\n   172→\n   173→---\n   174→\n   175→## 10) Risks and Mitigations\n   176→\n   177→### Risk: Scope Expansion\n   178→- Mitigation: strict V1 boundary; defer social/gamification features\n   179→\n   180→### Risk: Multiplayer Jackpot Fairness Complexity\n   181→- Mitigation: isolate acceptance criteria for entry weighting, winner selection, and VRF verification early\n   182→\n   183→### Risk: First-Game Delivery Risk\n   184→- Mitigation: use Coinflip as first implementation target, then add Lord of the RNGs after core settlement and fairness flows are proven\n   185→\n   186→### Risk: Integration Drift from Existing Repo\n   187→- Mitigation: keep standard Anchor path (per-game + shared crate), avoid parallel architecture tracks\n   188→\n   189→### Risk: Wallet UX Friction\n   190→- Mitigation: ship stable normal wallet flow first; evaluate embedded wallet in V1.5\n   191→\n   192→---\n   193→\n   194→## 11) Success Metrics (V1)\n   195→\n   196→Primary:\n   197→- Successful completion rate of game rounds/matches\n   198→- Settlement correctness and claim success rate\n   199→- Fairness verification usage and pass rate\n   200→- Critical error rate within acceptable threshold\n   201→\n   202→Secondary:\n   203→- Early retention and repeat play behavior\n   204→- Time-to-complete for core game loop\n   205→\n   206→---\n   207→\n   208→## 12) Post-Launch Expansion\n   209→\n   210→### V1.5\n   211→- Chat (no rewards)\n   212→- Intro quests\n   213→- Simple points layer\n   214→- Embedded wallet rollout option\n   215→\n   216→### V2\n   217→- Chat rewards\n   218→- Boss raids\n   219→- Advanced quests and gamification depth\n   220→- Additional game(s)\n   221→- Referral system and broader social loops\n   222→\n   223→---\n   224→\n   225→## 13) Scope Governance\n   226→\n   227→- Any feature not listed under V1 In Scope is excluded by default.\n   228→- Deferred features require explicit re-prioritization after launch readiness review.\n   229→- Changes to custody model or architecture path require a separate decision memo.\n   230→\n   231→---\n   232→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e756669-5013-49f4-827b-46f540129d9e","uuid":"1641d2d1-c242-4044-99ea-c263d7671546","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/SCOPE.md","content":"# RNG Utopia - Scope\n\nNon-custodial P2P gaming platform on Solana, scoped for practical V1 execution.\n\n---\n\n## 1) Scope Goal\n\nDeliver a launchable V1 focused on:\n- Two core games\n- On-chain settlement\n- Verifiable fairness\n- Basic player history/profile\n\nThis document defines what is in scope, out of scope, and deferred. It intentionally avoids implementation-level details.\n\n---\n\n## 2) Product Scope\n\n### In Scope (V1 Launch)\n- Lord of the RNGs\n- Coinflip\n- Wallet connection (normal Solana wallet flow first)\n- Non-custodial transaction flow for all financial actions\n- Fairness verification experience for each game\n- Basic user profile and history views\n- Basic operational controls (pause/resume, monitoring, incident response)\n\n### Out of Scope (V1 Launch)\n- Internal custodial balance model\n- Multi-chain support\n- Token launch and token utility\n- Referrals/rakeback programs\n- Lootboxes\n- Profile customization/social linking\n\n### Deferred to V1.5 / V2\n- Global chat\n- Chat rewards\n- Boss raids\n- Deep quests system\n- Advanced gamification loops\n- Expanded social features\n\n---\n\n## 3) Architecture Direction (Locked)\n\n### Core Decisions\n- Chain: Solana\n- Custody: Non-custodial\n- Program model: Standard Anchor programs (per-game + shared crate, see `docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md`)\n- Wallet rollout: normal wallets first, embedded wallet expansion later\n\n### Explicit Constraint\n- Do not build a temporary minimal program with planned rewrite.\n- Continue on a single architecture path: program-per-game + shared Rust crate (`solana/shared/`). See pivot doc (`docs/pivot-doc.md`).\n\n---\n\n## 4) Source of Truth and Boundaries\n\n### On-Chain Source of Truth\n- All money movement\n- Round settlement outcomes\n- Payout eligibility and claim state\n\n### Off-Chain Responsibilities\n- Read models and indexing for UX/performance\n- Basic profile/history aggregation\n- Fairness presentation and verification UX\n- Real-time coordination where needed for UX\n\n### Rule\n- If it changes user funds or determines payouts, it must be validated on-chain.\n\n---\n\n## 5) V1 Game Scope\n\n### Lord of the RNGs (V1)\n- Multiplayer tier participation with multiple entries per player\n- VRF-backed wheel spin resolution\n- Round settlement and claim flow\n- Fairness verification path (VRF-backed result visibility)\n\n### Coinflip (V1)\n- Match creation/join flow\n- Randomness-driven outcome\n- Settlement and claim flow\n- Fairness verification path (VRF-backed result visibility)\n\n### Shared Game Requirements\n- Idempotent action handling\n- Replay protection for signed actions\n- Clear error states for failed transactions\n- Devnet-first validation before any production rollout\n\n---\n\n## 6) Functional Requirements (V1)\n\n- Users can connect wallets and perform game actions\n- All financial interactions are on-chain\n- Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs are playable end-to-end\n- Users can verify fairness for completed rounds/matches\n- Users can view basic profile and recent history\n- Operators can pause/resume games\n\n---\n\n## 7) Non-Functional Requirements (V1)\n\n- Reliability: stable under expected early load\n- Observability: errors and key events are visible\n- Security baseline: rate limiting, validation, abuse protections\n- UX baseline: clear transaction state feedback and recovery paths\n- Operational readiness: incident checklist and rollback procedure\n\n---\n\n## 8) Delivery Plan\n\n### Phase 0 - Alignment and Readiness\n- Confirm architecture decisions and provider selections\n- Confirm game-level acceptance criteria\n- Finalize launch scope freeze\n\n### Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End\n- Complete real Coinflip game loop with on-chain settlement\n- Deliver fairness verification view for Coinflip\n- Validate on devnet with end-to-end flows\n\n### Phase 2 - Lord of the RNGs End-to-End\n- Complete real Lord of the RNGs game loop with on-chain settlement\n- Deliver fairness verification view for Lord of the RNGs\n- Validate on devnet with end-to-end flows\n\n### Phase 3 - Profile/History + Ops Hardening\n- Basic player profile/history from indexed data\n- Operational controls, alerting, and runbook\n- Stability pass and launch readiness checks\n\n### Phase 4 - Launch Gate\n- Devnet validation complete\n- Scope lock maintained\n- No critical blockers remaining\n\n---\n\n## 9) Launch Readiness Checklist (V1)\n\n### Functional\n- [ ] Wallet connection works for launch wallet path\n- [ ] Lord of the RNGs playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n- [ ] Coinflip playable end-to-end with real settlement path\n- [ ] Fairness verification works for Lord of the RNGs\n- [ ] Fairness verification works for Coinflip\n- [ ] Basic profile/history available and accurate\n\n### Security and Integrity\n- [ ] On-chain payout invariants validated\n- [ ] Idempotency and replay protections validated\n- [ ] Critical abuse paths mitigated\n- [ ] Emergency pause tested\n\n### Operational\n- [ ] Monitoring and error reporting active\n- [ ] Incident and rollback playbook documented\n- [ ] Devnet soak tests completed\n\n---\n\n## 10) Risks and Mitigations\n\n### Risk: Scope Expansion\n- Mitigation: strict V1 boundary; defer social/gamification features\n\n### Risk: Multiplayer Jackpot Fairness Complexity\n- Mitigation: isolate acceptance criteria for entry weighting, winner selection, and VRF verification early\n\n### Risk: First-Game Delivery Risk\n- Mitigation: use Coinflip as first implementation target, then add Lord of the RNGs after core settlement and fairness flows are proven\n\n### Risk: Integration Drift from Existing Repo\n- Mitigation: keep standard Anchor path (per-game + shared crate), avoid parallel architecture tracks\n\n### Risk: Wallet UX Friction\n- Mitigation: ship stable normal wallet flow first; evaluate embedded wallet in V1.5\n\n---\n\n## 11) Success Metrics (V1)\n\nPrimary:\n- Successful completion rate of game rounds/matches\n- Settlement correctness and claim success rate\n- Fairness verification usage and pass rate\n- Critical error rate within acceptable threshold\n\nSecondary:\n- Early retention and repeat play behavior\n- Time-to-complete for core game loop\n\n---\n\n## 12) Post-Launch Expansion\n\n### V1.5\n- Chat (no rewards)\n- Intro quests\n- Simple points layer\n- Embedded wallet rollout option\n\n### V2\n- Chat rewards\n- Boss raids\n- Advanced quests and gamification depth\n- Additional game(s)\n- Referral system and broader social loops\n\n---\n\n## 13) Scope Governance\n\n- Any feature not listed under V1 In Scope is excluded by default.\n- Deferred features require explicit re-prioritization after launch readiness review.\n- Changes to custody model or architecture path require a separate decision memo.\n\n---\n","numLines":232,"startLine":1,"totalLines":232}}}
